article.description: Rodney Pryor scored 23 points, LJ Peak added 22 and Georgetown held off Elon 77-74 on Sunday.
article.headline: Pryor, Peak help Georgetown hold off Elon 77-74
article.linkText: Pryor, Peak help Georgetown hold off Elon 77-74
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Rodney Pryor scored 23 points, LJ Peak added 22 and Georgetown held off Elon 77-74 on Sunday. The Hoyas continually surged ahead with the Phoenix coming back. The game was tied at 36 at halftime but a dunk by Pryor put Georgetown up 52-41 less than five minutes into the second half. Sheldon Eberhardt and Brian Dawkins had 3-pointers in an 8-0 surge for Elon but the Phoenix never got over the hump. A Dawkins 3-pointer made it a one-point game at 8:49, but a 3 by the Hoyas' Tre Campbell put the lead at 76-68 with 2:58 to go. Elon had one last surge and Luke Eddy's layup with 15 seconds left made it a one-possession game. Dawkins finished with 17 points for Elon, which shot 42 percent but made 11 3's, and Luke Eddy had 12. Jesse Govan added 13 points for the Hoyas.
